## DEPRECATED: Store global patterns using project_id='_global_'

**DEPRECATED (2026-01-01):** This pattern is obsolete. Global patterns now use `project_id=NULL`.

The `_global_` project was removed. Use `project_id=None` in code or `GLOBAL_SCOPE` sentinel for queries.

See migration `040_nullable_pattern_project.sql`.

*Original rationale: Using a specific project ID simplifies global pattern storage and avoids complex schema changes.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 7804a3f0-a2e5-4dc1-a741-a070916345da | Applied: 2025-12-28T16:17:59.503659 | DEPRECATED: 2026-01-01 -->

## Limit JSON edits to designated fields during structured workflows

When modifying JSON files in a structured workflow, only edit the 'passes' field or other fields explicitly specified in the task instructions.  Avoid unintended changes to maintain project integrity.

*Rationale: Restricting edits prevents accidental modifications and ensures the integrity of structured data.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 7bad11a0-085a-4dbe-8c82-15d78460e5a9 | Applied: 2025-12-28T16:17:59.539164 -->


## Standardize HealthReport dataclass and API Response fields

Implement the `HealthReport` dataclass with fields `status`, `corrections`, `warnings`, `metrics`, `stale_rules`, `auto_archived`, and `timestamp`. Update the `HealthResponse` model in `backend/app/api/memory.py` to include `stale_rules` and `auto_archived` fields for consistency.

*Rationale: Observed in sessions 00dda86f and 985adc77 as part of context-memory-v2 to ensure uniform reporting across the system.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 757302a6-944b-4b6a-ab46-e6e9c63703ff | Applied: 2025-12-28T18:37:41.804781 -->


## Feed structural findings into rule adherence observations

During the exploration phase of refactoring (Step 6c), feed high-severity structural findings into rule adherence observations. Map these findings to specific architecture rules in `.claude/rules/` for future context injection.

*Rationale: New mandatory step added to the refactoring workflow to improve long-term rule compliance tracking.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 168d70ff-f15c-4dc9-84bb-253222d189a0 | Applied: 2025-12-28T20:49:06.726502 -->

## Stage files after 'git stash pop' before pushing

When popping a stash during a rebase workflow, always run `git add .` and `git commit` before `git push`. Git push will report 'Everything up-to-date' and fail to upload changes if files are only in the working directory.

*Rationale: Observed failure where a push succeeded without uploading local changes restored via stash pop.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 26d96b78-af4f-4867-adb3-9a0aadeebede | Applied: 2025-12-28T20:49:06.758154 -->

## Modularize large Claude command markdown files

Reduce core command file size by extracting embedded bash scripts and JSON examples into the structured directory `~/.claude/commands/<command_name>/`. Target a file size reduction of ~50% for the primary markdown definition.

*Rationale: Successful modularization of refactor_it.md improved maintainability and followed the project's refactor plan.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 8c3d0652-82b4-411e-8efc-b3d83053f8bb | Applied: 2025-12-28T20:49:06.792965 -->


## Use connection context manager for database access

Always access the database via the connection generator context manager: `with get_connection() as conn:`. This ensures consistent resource management across API requests and tasks.

*Rationale: Entry 1 identifies this as a standard project architecture for managing `psycopg.Connection` lifecycles.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 9e7e4800-6298-49c8-a24d-bc881fd2fe2c | Applied: 2025-12-28T21:51:51.190870 -->

## Consolidate project-agnostic Claude configurations to global directory

Store project-agnostic Claude commands (like `/next_it`, `/update_it`) and interaction rules in `~/.claude/` rather than project-specific folders. Update internal references to point to these global definitions.

*Rationale: Entry 3 establishes this to eliminate redundancy and configuration drift across multiple projects (portfolio-ai, summitflow).*

<!-- Pattern ID: ce14c34f-83c0-499a-a195-bd88c7bbb6c9 | Applied: 2025-12-28T21:51:51.233685 -->


## Archiving completed tasks to completed directory

Maintain project hygiene by moving completed feature implementation files (plans, prompts, and implementation JSON) into the `tasks/completed/` subdirectory. Use `git mv` to preserve file history.

*Rationale: Observed in session 687d50d0 as a standard cleanup and audit trail procedure.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 78d0e7e7-49aa-4bc6-a500-7e9746d40ddf | Applied: 2025-12-29T17:26:22.875602 -->


## Standardized Primary and Secondary LLM Model Selection

Use 'claude-sonnet-4-5' as the primary model for complex logic and 'gemini-3-flash-preview' as the secondary/fallback model. Configure these via 'PATCH /{project_id}' using fields 'claude_model' and 'gemini_model'.

*Rationale: Defined as a project-level configuration and strictly baked into prompts and storage schemas.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 01913957-c7dd-4816-81c9-dc23139fb339 | Applied: 2025-12-30T16:20:29.775061 -->


## Task Table Schema for Automated Execution

The 'tasks' table must include columns: 'claimed_by' (text), 'claimed_at' (timestamp), 'claim_expires_at' (timestamp), and 'tier' (text) to support agent-based claiming and expiration logic.

*Rationale: New schema requirements identified for the Phase 2 Execution Pipeline architecture.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 5c152b71-17bd-4304-a91c-d07065601aac | Applied: 2025-12-30T19:53:38.679074 -->

## Standardized Git Commit Message Template and Hook Verification

Use the template at '~/.gitmessage' with format 'type(scope): subject

body for WHY

Refs: TASK-xxx'. Verify frontend changes using ESLint, tsc, and Prettier hooks before pushing to main.

*Rationale: Entry 3 refined the implementation plan for git workflow audits and specified the required template format and hook verification steps.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 80b23649-8308-4b0a-a85b-69f695568881 | Applied: 2025-12-30T19:53:38.712519 -->

## Avoid generic dict types in storage layer

Do not use `list[dict]` or `dict[str, Any]` for complex data structures in the storage layer. Define Pydantic models or `TypedDicts` to ensure type safety and proper IDE support.

*Rationale: Entry 1 explicitly identified the heavy usage of generic types as a refactoring target due to lack of type safety.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 69b20043-845a-4e78-ba2a-a6fa9855e9f0 | Applied: 2025-12-30T19:53:38.747451 -->


## Document task discoveries in spec-it-notes.md

After completing each task in the TDD foundation phase, append all technical insights, discoveries, and process changes to `tasks/tdd-foundation/spec-it-notes.md`. This log is required for the eventual implementation of the `/spec_it` command.

*Rationale: Session 48f45664 updated prompt.md to make this a critical rule, and eb6a4bae successfully used it to track 35 new insertions.*

<!-- Pattern ID: e45e81f7-5e70-4a6d-8201-3464e7187763 | Applied: 2025-12-30T20:57:05.973328 -->


## Schema definition for capabilities table

The `public.capabilities` table must contain the following columns: `id` (uuid), `project_id` (text), `component_id` (text), `capability_id` (text), `name` (text), `description` (text), `priority` (int, default 2), `status` (text, default 'pending'), and `locked_at` (timestamp). Use these fields when querying project capability states.

*Rationale: Database schema was explicitly identified during a capabilities audit in session 753acc03-397d-4077-814e-905d270d4b12.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 2bb5834f-04a0-483e-9a97-00c8c1beec86 | Applied: 2025-12-30T22:58:58.981715 -->


## Cast UUIDs to strings before JSON serialization

Explicitly cast UUID observation IDs to strings using `str(uuid_val)` before inclusion in dictionaries destined for JSON serialization or task generation. This prevents `TypeError: Object of type UUID is not JSON serializable` in task storage and generation layers.

*Rationale: Task generation failed due to unhandled UUID objects in JSON-bound data structures.*

<!-- Pattern ID: f859d920-8cc4-404f-895b-ec8db0509eae | Applied: 2025-12-31T10:20:29.790456 -->


## JSON-First Task Schema for AI Reliability

Transition task definitions from Markdown-style descriptions to a JSON-first schema to improve AI agent performance. Include structured fields for `phases` and `acceptance_criteria` to prevent agents from incorrectly overwriting task files.

*Rationale: Architectural shift identified in entry 92937835 to solve issues with AI models overwriting Markdown files.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 6948f924-f4aa-4b53-9ba6-cab31ff2016d | Applied: 2025-12-31T13:17:41.909795 -->

## CLI Configuration Singleton Implementation

Implement the CLI configuration module in `backend/cli/config.py` using a frozen dataclass and `@lru_cache` for a singleton instance. Centralize retrieval of `ST_API_BASE` (default: `http://localhost:8001/api`) and `ST_PROJECT_ID` (default: `summitflow`) from environment variables.

*Rationale: Observed in success entry 30605e3c as the foundational architecture for the new Python CLI migration.*

<!-- Pattern ID: bb1a63d6-fa2e-44bd-9217-cbb4c0912c0e | Applied: 2025-12-31T13:17:41.943368 -->


## Context-Triggered Automated Checkpoint Commits

Trigger an automated git commit when the AI context window reaches 95% capacity. This checkpoint must capture updates in documentation and task prompts to preserve state before context limits are reached.

*Rationale: Operational safeguard used to prevent data loss during long-running sessions with heavy context usage.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 98488283-57fc-470b-8bfa-d420c99da127 | Applied: 2025-12-31T16:43:49.649587 -->

## Use get_effective_criteria Helper for Task Retrieval

Use the `get_effective_criteria` function in the `ImplementationExecutor` to source criteria from either specific capabilities or individual tasks. Do not use direct JSONB parsing of the criteria field to ensure robustness across different task sources.

*Rationale: Architecture refactoring in session 503556a4 replaced direct parsing with this more robust helper method.*

<!-- Pattern ID: ae9a1c95-6012-4600-824e-79bcdec067f6 | Applied: 2025-12-31T16:43:49.688787 -->


## Partial Success Response Strategy for Batch API Endpoints

API batch endpoints (/components/batch, /capabilities/batch, /tasks/batch) must handle partial failures by returning a JSON object containing a 'created' list (successful IDs or objects) and an 'errors' list (failed items with descriptions). This ensures the system can optimize performance via bulk requests while maintaining granular error reporting.

*Rationale: Implemented in session 6c229199 to optimize system initialization and handle failures gracefully.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 47f44058-4467-4059-a5f0-28c4a398dcde | Applied: 2025-12-31T17:24:53.185669 -->


## Evidence UI Visual Metadata Standards

In `EvidenceTab.tsx`, render 'Auto-captured' status with the `Bot` icon and 'Test run' associations with the `TestTube` icon. Use `text-2xs text-slate-500 truncate max-w-[200px]` for criterion text display with an HTML `title` attribute for the full description.

*Rationale: Successful UI refactoring patterns identified in 51877334.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 75ef41f0-5a64-4d80-9928-d2dea40d396c | Applied: 2025-12-31T18:12:25.157171 -->

## Standardized Evidence Selection and Mapping

Use the `EVIDENCE_SELECT_WITH_CRITERION` constant in `backend/app/storage/evidence.py` to perform a `LEFT JOIN` on `acceptance_criteria`. Use the `_row_to_evidence` mapper to populate `criterion_text`, ensuring the UI can display descriptions instead of just IDs.

*Rationale: Observed in session 51877334 as a successful strategy for improving evidence data context in the frontend.*

<!-- Pattern ID: aec69d2f-5f59-4d88-9633-41ba5f1b326c | Applied: 2025-12-31T18:12:25.198656 -->


## Standardize Subtasks Storage Module in backend/app/storage/subtasks.py

Implement subtask persistence in `backend/app/storage/subtasks.py` using functions: `create_subtask`, `get_subtasks_for_task`, `update_subtask_passes`, `delete_subtasks_for_task`, `bulk_create_subtasks`, and `get_subtask_summary`. The `task_subtasks` table must include columns: `id`, `task_id`, `subtask_id`, `phase`, `description`, `steps`, and `display_order`.

*Rationale: The subtasks storage module architecture was explicitly defined and implemented to support task enrichment workflows.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 907e67a9-aade-4907-8846-19e9904c1376 | Applied: 2025-12-31T20:26:51.435070 -->


## Worktree Directory Structure and Isolation

Configure the `WorktreeManager` to use `/tmp/summitflow-worktrees/` as the base directory for isolated tasks. Use the `exec` branch prefix and ensure `create_worktree` removes existing target directories before creation to prevent stale path conflicts.

*Rationale: Standardizes the isolation strategy for autonomous tasks and ensures recovery from previously failed attempts.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 0f86b8aa-d049-4707-8177-bd9916b557e3 | Applied: 2025-12-31T23:24:05.460097 -->

## Git Commit Retry Logic for Modifying Hooks

In `WorktreeManager.commit_in_worktree`, implement a retry loop with `max_retries=2`. If a commit fails because pre-commit hooks modified files, re-stage the changes using `git add` and attempt the commit again to ensure the worktree state is preserved.

*Rationale: Pre-commit hooks that modify files (like formatters) cause commits to fail; the retry mechanism ensures successful persistence in isolated worktrees.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 98822965-5e83-43c4-8a50-c1abba8b7582 | Applied: 2025-12-31T23:24:05.499384 -->

## Worktree ID Sanitization for Security

Apply the private `_sanitize_id` method in `WorktreeManager` to all task and project identifiers before use in shell or git commands. This prevents path traversal and shell injection by validating that identifiers contain only safe characters.

*Rationale: Security audit in entry 111e5199 identified risks of injection and traversal; implementation of sanitization fixed these vulnerabilities.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 8eff4ddc-2f28-44c7-ae8b-489fe071f35a | Applied: 2025-12-31T23:24:05.531670 -->


## Avoid Obsolete Task Fields and Legacy Result Classes

Do not use `spec_content` or `current_criterion_id` fields in Task schemas or frontend interfaces. Avoid the legacy `VerifyResult` class; use `VerifyResultV2` for all task verification logic to maintain compatibility with the TDD remediation plan.

*Rationale: Recent sessions identified these fields as technical debt and explicitly removed them from both backend and frontend layers.*

<!-- Pattern ID: a1adca5d-4fba-4523-b24a-e0fd5265e111 | Applied: 2026-01-01T04:23:54.556084 -->

## Database Schema Authority and Synchronization

Treat database migrations as the authoritative source of truth. The file `backend/app/storage/schema.py` must only be used as a fallback; manually synchronize it after applying migrations to include new columns like `claimed_by` or `verification_result`.

*Rationale: The system explicitly clarified that migrations are authoritative while schema.py is a fallback after a successful synchronization effort.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 8bb71e9e-68de-4538-a73c-30b1f6b061f2 | Applied: 2026-01-01T04:23:54.588403 -->


## DEPRECATED: Store refactor task lists in 'tasks.plan_content' JSONB column

**DEPRECATED (2026-01-01):** This pattern is obsolete. The `plan_content` column is no longer used.

All commands (/refactor_it, /do_it, /task_it) now use normalized tables:
- `task_subtasks` - Subtask definitions with phase, description, display_order
- `task_subtask_steps` - Individual steps with `passes` tracking per step

**Migration:** See migration 039_task_subtask_steps.sql.
**New pattern:** Use POST /subtasks/batch and POST /steps/batch APIs instead of PATCH plan_content.

*Original rationale: Entry be44d4ae explicitly documents this distinction to prevent data loss when mixing task types.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 00fe9d77-50fb-4cb3-8648-f36a173f8053 | Applied: 2026-01-01T08:42:09.530932 | DEPRECATED: 2026-01-01 -->

## Use task_subtask_steps table for step-level tracking

All task execution (/refactor_it, /do_it, /task_it) must use the normalized `task_subtask_steps` table for step-level tracking:

1. **Create steps:** `POST /subtasks/{subtask_id}/steps/batch` with `{"descriptions": ["Step 1", "Step 2"]}`
2. **Mark step complete:** `PATCH /subtasks/{subtask_id}/steps/{step_number}` with `{"passes": true}`
3. **Mark subtask complete:** `PATCH /subtasks/{subtask_id}` with `{"passes": true}` (after all steps pass)
4. **Fetch with steps:** `GET /subtasks?include_steps=true` returns `steps_from_table` with individual tracking

This enforces granular AI accountability - each step must be explicitly marked via API.

*Rationale: Steps table normalization completed 2026-01-01. See migration 039_task_subtask_steps.sql.*

<!-- Pattern ID: steps-table-normalization-2026-01-01 | Applied: 2026-01-01T10:15:00.000000 -->

## Use 'capability_status' key for CLI capability verification responses

When parsing JSON responses from the capability verification API (endpoint `/api/projects/{project_id}/capabilities/{id}/verify`), extract the status using the key 'capability_status' instead of 'status'. The CLI command logic must reflect this schema to correctly report test outcomes.

*Rationale: Entry 718f2228 highlights a bug fix where the CLI was incorrectly looking for 'status' in a response that uses 'capability_status'.*

<!-- Pattern ID: ab5c0a2f-f7ae-4dc0-93bc-aa9ce251fc9b | Applied: 2026-01-01T08:42:09.563970 -->


## Tmux Session Naming for Development Workspace

Standardize development environment sessions using `claude-summitflow` for the primary project workspace and `claude-terminal` for standard terminal operations. Use `tmux ls` to verify both sessions are active and attached for background task persistence.

*Rationale: Entry 467e8b24 validates that these specific session names ensure the development environment is correctly initialized and persistent.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 3f7c5e69-1f7e-4e3a-86c3-9449a630778d | Applied: 2026-01-01T09:46:43.571754 -->

## Subtask Step API Routing and Schema Standards

Define subtask step API routes at `/api/projects/{project_id}/tasks/{task_id}/subtasks/{subtask_id}/steps`. Store Pydantic models in `backend/app/schemas/steps.py` and use the helper function `_get_subtask_table_id` for backend database table resolution.

*Rationale: Entry c321f8f0 details API expansion for subtasks and specific requirements for schema organization and helper function usage.*

<!-- Pattern ID: bcd27663-bf3d-4496-a602-ba5c9c516ff6 | Applied: 2026-01-01T09:46:43.608419 -->


## SummitFlow Service Status Verification

Verify all services are healthy using `systemctl status summitflow-celery.service` for background workers. Validate the following local endpoints: Frontend (http://localhost:3001), Backend API (http://localhost:8001), PostgreSQL (localhost:5432), and Terminal Service (http://localhost:3002).

*Rationale: Session 50973fc6 established a specific set of ports and service names for project verification.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 8d908b21-7b2f-40dc-94b2-adc70d66c39a | Applied: 2026-01-01T12:24:38.439001 -->


## Use get_task to Bypass Pagination in VALIDATION_MODE

When the system is in `VALIDATION_MODE`, fetch allowed task IDs directly via `get_task(task_id)` instead of using `list_ready_tasks(limit=50)`. This ensures that tasks outside the standard pagination limit are correctly retrieved and processed during automated validation scenarios.

*Rationale: Diary entry f92edbd9-f494-4328-be3a-affc6399d3e1 records a fix where task limits were incorrectly applied during validation, leading to skipped tasks.*

<!-- Pattern ID: fef13f88-b475-443d-a080-4c93a0e182ef | Applied: 2026-01-01T16:23:54.538856 -->


## Schema for learned_patterns Table

Define the learned_patterns table using UUID primary keys and JSONB for source_diary_ids and source_observation_ids. Required fields are project_id (UUID or NULL), pattern_type, title, and content to maintain links between patterns and original diaries.

*Rationale: Establishes a flexible architectural choice for storing distilled memory patterns with their source references.*

<!-- Pattern ID: b70160e6-dab8-4a01-bba6-d4f33330be3e | Applied: 2026-01-01T19:27:39.888080 -->

## High-Depth Interview Protocol for /spec_it

Prioritize an extensive interview phase of 20-40 questions within the /spec_it workflow. Follow the pipeline: Automated Discovery -> Gap Analysis (Current vs Desired) -> AskUserQuestion -> Finalize Spec to build comprehensive project context.

*Rationale: User preference for deep, non-obvious questioning to build a comprehensive project context, inspired by the Tariq methodology.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 2aeb54a2-725e-4372-a4fb-218f65fdb7fc | Applied: 2026-01-01T19:27:39.927290 -->

## Separate /spec_it Discovery from /tdd_it Test Structuring

Use /spec_it exclusively for project discovery, automated codebase exploration, and user interviews. Use /tdd_it for defining component capabilities and test linking. This separation ensures discovery-first specification before implementation begins.

*Rationale: Architectural shift to clarify workflow phases and prevent premature coding before full project context is established.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 0a5ef3fa-5f89-4070-910f-9f6db9844cce | Applied: 2026-01-01T19:27:39.966162 -->


## Queryable Database Table Authority

Restrict database queries to confirmed active tables in the public schema: `accepted_specs`, `agent_checkpoints`, `notifications`, `terminal_sessions`, `session_diary`, `learned_patterns`, `tasks`, and `capabilities`. Do not attempt to access defunct tables like `scanner_database`, `scanner_api`, or `file_audit`.

*Rationale: Session 1 verified that multiple legacy scanner tables no longer exist in the public schema.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 6717aca2-fcba-433a-b089-7ae03ae04642 | Applied: 2026-01-01T22:51:01.400964 -->

## Orphaned Git Worktree Cleanup and Path Reset

Run `git worktree prune` to clear metadata for deleted task worktrees. Before creating new task worktrees in `/tmp/summitflow-worktrees/`, check for and remove stale directories at the target path to prevent isolation failures.

*Rationale: Session 2 required manual cleanup of orphaned worktrees to resolve execution bottlenecks.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 17a8ea90-e2b0-486a-b6a5-a5a3e24302d1 | Applied: 2026-01-01T22:51:01.440427 -->

## Disable redundant bug task generation in self-healing scans

Set `generate_bug_tasks=False` in self-healing flow implementations to prevent the creation of junk tasks. Automated scan results should directly trigger issue resolution and task closure without intermediate bug-report generation.

*Rationale: Validated as successful logic change in Session 2 to prevent redundant task creation.*

<!-- Pattern ID: b7c5f2c4-effa-495d-9f1b-939750821d4d | Applied: 2026-01-01T22:51:01.475411 -->


## Throttling Metrics in Observation Logs

Include the `throttled` item count in the `observation_queue_processing_completed` log event within the observation processor task to improve visibility into rate-limiting performance.

*Rationale: Ensures monitoring of how the new extraction throttle affects background processing.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 33c9ac6b-c8fa-4006-a8c8-487f90f8b8db | Applied: 2026-01-01T23:48:08.939106 -->

## Required Extraction Fields for ProjectAgentConfig

Add `extraction_enabled: bool` and `extraction_rpm_limit: int` to `ProjectAgentConfig` and `ProjectAgentConfigUpdate` interfaces. In the UI at `/projects/[id]/settings`, use the `ExtractionThrottlePanel` component with `rpm_limit_stops: [0, 5, 10, 15, 30, 60]` where 0 represents 'Off'.

*Rationale: Standardizes the implementation of data extraction rate limiting across the project settings and API.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 962d327b-6836-45b1-bdb5-1bab112d2a91 | Applied: 2026-01-01T23:48:08.974623 -->


## Progressive Disclosure for Memory Patterns using JSONL

Use `PatternService.format_pattern_jsonl()` to serialize memory patterns. Implement a progressive disclosure strategy: use the 'index' format (~14 tokens) for initial LLM context injection to fit up to 50 patterns within a 500-token budget, and fetch the 'full' representation (~51 tokens) only when specific detail is required.

*Rationale: Benchmarks show index format reduces token usage by 72% (14 vs 51 tokens), significantly optimizing the context window for large numbers of patterns.*

<!-- Pattern ID: 65451bcb-1088-4f66-89eb-bc04edb34d27 | Applied: 2026-01-02T12:26:21.090593 -->
